qas.question: In what century did the Tibetan Empire fall?
Who signed multiple peace treaties with the Tang?
What did one of the treaties between the Tang and Tibet help fix?

answers.text: the borders between Tibet and China

qas.question: Who was the Tangs biggest rival?
What year did Tang and Tibet sign a treaty to fix the borders?

context: <a3_0>Tibet<a3_0/> was once a strong power contemporaneous with Tang China (618–907). Until the Tibetan Empire's collapse in <a0_0>the 9th century<a0_0/>, it was the Tang's major rival in dominating Inner Asia. <a1_0>The Yarlung rulers of Tibet<a1_0/> also signed various peace treaties with the Tang, culminating in a treaty in <a4_0>821<a4_0/> that fixed <a2_0>the borders between Tibet and China<a2_0/>.
